1
00:00:11,958 --> 00:00:15,250
[FUTARO] I can't believe
they each bombed four subjects.

2
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:16,375
Great.

3
00:00:16,458 --> 00:00:18,291
I know we didn't have much time,

4
00:00:18,375 --> 00:00:19,958
but all of them studied so hard!

5
00:00:20,041 --> 00:00:23,625
Futaro! There's no talking about
school at the dinner table!

6
00:00:23,708 --> 00:00:25,375
What kind of dumb rule is that?

7
00:00:25,458 --> 00:00:28,250
Besides, you were the one
who hooked me up with this job!

8
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:31,000
You weren't always the whiz-kid
you are today, remember?

9
00:00:31,083 --> 00:00:34,500
They'll get there.
Try not to worry so much.

10
00:00:34,583 --> 00:00:36,208
Huh?

11
00:00:36,291 --> 00:00:38,500
Wow, you mean there was a time
when Futaro wasn't a huge nerd?

12
00:00:38,583 --> 00:00:42,000
Oh, yeah. In fact, your big bro
was a regular troublemaker,

13
00:00:42,083 --> 00:00:43,000
same as his old man.

14
00:00:43,083 --> 00:00:44,541
Really?

15
00:00:44,625 --> 00:00:47,333
And don't think I don't know
about that old photo

16
00:00:47,416 --> 00:00:49,333
you keep tucked
in your student handbook.

17
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:50,750
-Show me!
-Hell no.

18
00:00:50,833 --> 00:00:52,375
I'm not gonna let-- Uh!

19
00:00:52,458 --> 00:00:55,375
-Gotcha!
-Hey! Dad!

20
00:00:55,458 --> 00:00:58,000
Yay! I wanna see it too!

21
00:00:58,083 --> 00:01:00,125
[ISANARI]
Now. Let's look.

22
00:01:00,208 --> 00:01:01,666
Whoa!

23
00:01:01,750 --> 00:01:04,291
That can't really be him,
can it? How?

24
00:01:04,375 --> 00:01:05,666
Ha, ha, ha!

25
00:01:05,750 --> 00:01:07,541
That was around the time
you met that little girl

26
00:01:07,625 --> 00:01:09,250
and became the way
you are today.

27
00:01:09,333 --> 00:01:11,041
♪

28
00:01:15,625 --> 00:01:18,250
Ugh. What are you
going on about?

29
00:01:19,791 --> 00:01:22,791
[RAIHA] So, spill! Was she
your first love or something?

30
00:01:22,875 --> 00:01:24,500
[FUTARO]
No, now drop it!

31
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,041
♪

32
00:02:57,125 --> 00:02:59,666
Hmm. What are these?

33
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:01,833
[MIKU]
Croquettes.

34
00:03:01,916 --> 00:03:04,833
[YOTSUBA] Really?
'Cause they look like rocks.

35
00:03:06,625 --> 00:03:08,208
[MIKU]
I know they taste good.

36
00:03:09,250 --> 00:03:10,583
Go ahead, try them.

37
00:03:10,666 --> 00:03:12,625
[YOTSUBA]
'Kay, twist my arm!

38
00:03:12,708 --> 00:03:14,000
[FUTARO]
Sweet, there's ohagi.

39
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:16,541
Down the hatch.

40
00:03:16,625 --> 00:03:17,583
[BOTH gulp]

41
00:03:21,166 --> 00:03:23,291
[FUTARO] Oh, it's a croquette!
Not bad!

42
00:03:23,375 --> 00:03:26,000
-Are you kidding, it's awful!
-Says you.

43
00:03:26,083 --> 00:03:28,125
You're just picky because
you're so wealthy and spoiled.

44
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:29,458
[YOTSUBA]
Oh, yeah?

45
00:03:29,541 --> 00:03:31,250
Well, you don't have
any taste at all!

46
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:32,833
Zero stars, Miku!

47
00:03:32,916 --> 00:03:34,166
-[MIKU] Which is it?
-[FUTARO sighs]

48
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:36,958
Yeah, yeah,
I'm a classless loser, I know.

49
00:03:37,041 --> 00:03:38,791
Now let's start reviewing
those exams.

50
00:03:38,875 --> 00:03:39,833
Wait!

51
00:03:39,916 --> 00:03:41,000
-[FUTARO] Hmm?
-[YOTSUBA] Hmm?

52
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:44,958
I'm gonna keep making them
until they taste perfect.

53
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:46,500
-[YOTSUBA/FUTARO] Uhh...
-[MIKU] So eat up!

54
00:03:48,125 --> 00:03:49,291
[FUTARO groans]

55
00:03:49,375 --> 00:03:51,458
[YOTSUBA]
How's your stomach, Uesugi?

56
00:03:51,541 --> 00:03:54,416
Miku should be back
with the medicine any time now.

57
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:55,541
[MIKU panting]

58
00:03:55,625 --> 00:03:57,666
-[stomach rumbles]
-[FUTARO groans]

59
00:03:57,750 --> 00:04:00,541
And I thought I'd get
some actual work done today.

60
00:04:00,625 --> 00:04:02,041
Guess not.

61
00:04:03,125 --> 00:04:05,583
That girl fed me
within an inch of my life.

62
00:04:07,416 --> 00:04:10,166
[YOTSUBA] Yeah. I feel like
I'm gonna pop.

63
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:13,458
This only happened because
you had to play food critic!

64
00:04:13,541 --> 00:04:15,583
I actually thought
they tasted pretty decent.

65
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:16,708
All you had to do was lie!

66
00:04:16,791 --> 00:04:18,583
Trust me, if I had
told her a lie,

67
00:04:18,666 --> 00:04:20,416
then Miku would have seen
right through it.

68
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:22,125
[sighs]

69
00:04:22,208 --> 00:04:24,625
Then say something vague like
they've got an intense flavor

70
00:04:24,708 --> 00:04:26,125
and leave it at that.

71
00:04:26,208 --> 00:04:30,541
Be vague! That's brilliant!
I've learned something!

72
00:04:30,625 --> 00:04:32,750
Okay, but that's not exactly
the kind of lesson

73
00:04:32,833 --> 00:04:34,250
I came here to teach you.

74
00:04:36,291 --> 00:04:38,041
-[NINO] Well, well!
-Huh?

75
00:04:38,125 --> 00:04:41,166
Are you napping
in someone else's house?

76
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:43,583
No, let me guess,
somebody drugged you.

77
00:04:43,666 --> 00:04:45,708
With the way
I'm feeling today,

78
00:04:45,791 --> 00:04:48,541
I think I might like
for somebody to give me drugs.

79
00:04:48,625 --> 00:04:50,916
[NINO]
Hmm. Whatever, I don't care.

80
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,000
Anyway, let's go out
and have lunch, Itsuki.

81
00:04:53,083 --> 00:04:54,333
[ITSUKI]
Um, okay.

82
00:04:54,416 --> 00:04:56,583
Crap! Yotsuba!

83
00:04:56,666 --> 00:04:59,833
Uh, yeah? What's going on?

84
00:04:59,916 --> 00:05:01,750
[FUTARO]
I need these two to stay here

85
00:05:01,833 --> 00:05:02,875
so they'll study.

86
00:05:02,958 --> 00:05:05,208
You can't let them
leave the house.

87
00:05:05,291 --> 00:05:06,708
[YOTSUBA]
What should I do?

88
00:05:06,791 --> 00:05:08,875
I don't know, lie to them
if you have to!

89
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:11,708
I'll do my best.

90
00:05:11,791 --> 00:05:13,875
Oh, yeah!
By the station, there's this--

91
00:05:13,958 --> 00:05:15,458
[YOTSUBA]
Wait, you guys, don't go!

92
00:05:15,541 --> 00:05:17,125
Look at poor Uesugi!

93
00:05:17,208 --> 00:05:18,541
He's suddenly come down
with some kind

94
00:05:18,625 --> 00:05:20,125
of terrible rare disease!

95
00:05:20,208 --> 00:05:22,291
We have to make him better!

96
00:05:22,375 --> 00:05:24,000
-[NINO] Huh?
-A disease?

97
00:05:24,083 --> 00:05:26,208
[FUTARO]
Come on, really?

98
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:30,750
You're a horrible liar!

99
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:33,166
[ITSUKI] Maybe he should go
to the hospital.

100
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:34,541
No! Uh, he can't,

101
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:36,250
-it's impossible!
-[ITSUKI] Huh?

102
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:39,250
It's the kind of disease
where you die if you move!

103
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:40,750
[FUTARO]
That escalated quickly!

104
00:05:40,833 --> 00:05:43,208
He'll die? That's too bad.

105
00:05:43,291 --> 00:05:45,791
-Let's go, Itsuki.
-Yeah, coming.

106
00:05:45,875 --> 00:05:49,291
[coughing violently]

107
00:05:51,291 --> 00:05:53,500
Uh-oh. I only moved a little,
and now look.

108
00:05:53,583 --> 00:05:55,041
That's bad!

109
00:05:55,125 --> 00:05:57,291
You need to lie back down
before it gets any worse!

110
00:06:00,625 --> 00:06:03,750
Eh, he can just take
some medicine and sleep it off.

111
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:05,416
Um. No need to go out,

112
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,541
you can have croquettes
for lunch!

113
00:06:07,625 --> 00:06:10,041
[NINO] On what planet
are those croquettes?

114
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:14,500
You should... Uh. Oh!

115
00:06:14,583 --> 00:06:17,666
You're good at cooking, right?
Make him some porridge!

116
00:06:19,291 --> 00:06:21,500
[FUTARO]
I'm sick because I ate too much.

117
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:22,875
Why would I need food?

118
00:06:22,958 --> 00:06:25,625
♪

119
00:06:25,708 --> 00:06:27,666
I guess that isn't
too much to ask for.

120
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:29,458
[FUTARO]
Now she starts being nice?

121
00:06:29,541 --> 00:06:32,000
You don't mind it
with eggs in it, do you?

122
00:06:32,083 --> 00:06:34,291
[FUTARO]
Uh, that's fine. Thank you.

123
00:06:34,375 --> 00:06:36,958
I figured you were sick when
I saw you lying on the floor,

124
00:06:37,041 --> 00:06:38,875
but I had no idea
it was this serious.

125
00:06:38,958 --> 00:06:42,333
Yotsuba? Is there anything
I can do to help him out?

126
00:06:42,416 --> 00:06:44,625
Let's see. Um...

127
00:06:44,708 --> 00:06:45,875
[gasps]

128
00:06:45,958 --> 00:06:47,958
Yeah, you should
probably hold his hand!

129
00:06:51,041 --> 00:06:53,083
Remember how Mom
would always do that for us

130
00:06:53,166 --> 00:06:54,875
whenever we were sick in bed?

131
00:06:54,958 --> 00:06:57,375
She said it was
a magical healing spell!

132
00:06:58,625 --> 00:06:59,833
That's different!

133
00:06:59,916 --> 00:07:02,166
This situation is
nothing like that, okay?

134
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:04,958
Yotsuba. Would you please
stop talking for five--

135
00:07:05,041 --> 00:07:07,416
-[grunts]
-Whoa, are you all right?

136
00:07:09,458 --> 00:07:11,666
[ITSUKI] Well, if it'll help
you get better.

137
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:12,916
[FUTARO]
What?

138
00:07:18,291 --> 00:07:19,625
[ITSUKI gasping]

139
00:07:21,708 --> 00:07:23,708
Nope, can't do it!

140
00:07:23,791 --> 00:07:26,708
[FUTARO] Wow, you must hate me
more than I thought.

141
00:07:27,833 --> 00:07:31,208
Okay. We got them
to stay in the house.

142
00:07:31,291 --> 00:07:32,666
Now what do I do?

143
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:34,708
[YOTSUBA] Try to get along
better, you two.

144
00:07:34,791 --> 00:07:37,666
♪

145
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:40,458
And I want you to study
with the group!

146
00:07:41,583 --> 00:07:44,916
Let's all take Uesugi's lessons
together from here on out!

147
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,916
It'll be a whole lot more fun
for everybody if we do!

148
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,666
♪

149
00:07:50,750 --> 00:07:52,625
[FUTARO] I approached this
the wrong way.

150
00:07:52,708 --> 00:07:54,291
It seems to be more effective
for Yotsuba

151
00:07:54,375 --> 00:07:56,833
to tell the truth
than to do something dishonest.

152
00:07:59,458 --> 00:08:01,250
I guess I'll think about it.

153
00:08:01,333 --> 00:08:04,291
Okay! The porridge is ready now.

154
00:08:05,833 --> 00:08:09,333
[gasping]

155
00:08:11,375 --> 00:08:12,791
[gasping]

156
00:08:12,875 --> 00:08:15,791
[FUTARO]
Oh, is that whole rice?

157
00:08:15,875 --> 00:08:18,750
Each individual grain
is sparkling.

158
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:21,333
They really do buy
the good stuff here, huh?

159
00:08:24,875 --> 00:08:27,625
[screaming]

160
00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:30,250
Oh, god, it's burning
my face off!

161
00:08:31,250 --> 00:08:33,208
Are you okay? I'm sor--

162
00:08:33,291 --> 00:08:36,333
Hey. I thought if you
moved around, you'd die.

163
00:08:36,416 --> 00:08:38,000
♪

164
00:08:38,083 --> 00:08:40,541
[gasps]

165
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:42,333
♪

166
00:08:42,416 --> 00:08:45,416
[chuckles nervously]
It's a miracle!

167
00:08:46,458 --> 00:08:48,750
Looks like it's you
and me again, Yotsuba.

168
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:50,208
[YOTSUBA chuckles awkwardly]

169
00:08:50,291 --> 00:08:52,833
Right back to where we started
before the exams.

170
00:08:52,916 --> 00:08:55,500
-I don't know about that.
-Huh?

171
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:57,375
[YOTSUBA]
Come on, haven't you noticed?

172
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:01,416
Normally, Nino would have tried
to find a way to kick you out,

173
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:03,208
but she didn't this time.

174
00:09:03,291 --> 00:09:04,875
[FUTARO]
That was a coincidence.

175
00:09:06,041 --> 00:09:08,166
[YOTSUBA] It's not just her
and Itsuki, either.

176
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:10,416
Ichika and Miku
are changing too.

177
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:12,833
Even I've picked up on it.

178
00:09:12,916 --> 00:09:15,958
I guess I'm the only one of us
who hasn't improved any.

179
00:09:16,041 --> 00:09:18,333
I mean, my grades
are still pretty sucky, right?

180
00:09:18,416 --> 00:09:20,083
[chuckles]

181
00:09:20,166 --> 00:09:21,958
I'm gonna have to disagree.

182
00:09:23,583 --> 00:09:26,250
You were actually
the first one to change.

183
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:28,333
I'm lucky that at least
one of you girls was honest

184
00:09:28,416 --> 00:09:29,666
and forthcoming with me.

185
00:09:30,750 --> 00:09:33,375
Then again, maybe I'm giving you
too much credit.

186
00:09:33,458 --> 00:09:35,041
The only reason
I'm sick right now

187
00:09:35,125 --> 00:09:37,666
is because of your aversion
to telling lies.

188
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:39,250
[YOTSUBA] Do you know
why I always help you

189
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:41,416
when you're trying to get
everyone to study with you?

190
00:09:42,666 --> 00:09:44,166
Well, that's no secret.

191
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:46,458
It's because you want
to get good grades.

192
00:09:46,541 --> 00:09:48,125
[YOTSUBA]
Not exactly.

193
00:09:48,208 --> 00:09:51,208
♪

194
00:09:55,250 --> 00:09:56,916
It's 'cause I like you.

195
00:09:58,333 --> 00:10:01,333
♪

196
00:10:07,083 --> 00:10:08,166
-[heartbeat pounding]
-[gasps]

197
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:12,708
You... do?

198
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:23,250
Fooled you. Ha!
I was just yankin' your chain!

199
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:25,500
That's what you get
for thinkin' I can't lie!

200
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:27,250
[laughs wildly]

201
00:10:28,541 --> 00:10:30,291
[FUTARO]
I will never trust again.

202
00:10:31,458 --> 00:10:33,250
[NARRATOR]
And so, on that day,

203
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:36,375
Futaro's already hardened heart
grew a little colder.

204
00:10:37,583 --> 00:10:39,375
[YOTSUBA singing]
Time to go camping!

205
00:10:39,458 --> 00:10:40,875
Time to go camping!

206
00:10:40,958 --> 00:10:42,833
Time to go camping--

207
00:10:45,958 --> 00:10:47,416
Hey, Uesugi!

208
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:49,708
The school camping trip
is coming up!

209
00:10:49,791 --> 00:10:52,625
Yotsuba.
[growls]

210
00:10:52,708 --> 00:10:54,333
[screaming]

211
00:10:56,416 --> 00:10:57,333
It's me.

212
00:10:57,416 --> 00:10:59,666
Oh, you scared me.

213
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:01,208
Who the heck is that?

214
00:11:02,291 --> 00:11:03,791
It's me again.

215
00:11:03,875 --> 00:11:05,208
I'm sorry.
I guess I forgot.

216
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:08,708
-He's gonna kill me!
-It's still me.

217
00:11:08,791 --> 00:11:10,250
Where's he keep coming from?

218
00:11:11,291 --> 00:11:13,916
-Somebody please help me!
-[clears throat]

219
00:11:17,041 --> 00:11:19,250
No shouting in the library.

220
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:20,541
-Sorry, ma'am.
-Sorry, ma'am.

221
00:11:21,625 --> 00:11:23,208
[YOTSUBA]
So, what are you doing

222
00:11:23,291 --> 00:11:25,333
with all these creepy
Halloween masks?

223
00:11:25,416 --> 00:11:27,875
[MIKU] He's helping organize
the test of courage.

224
00:11:27,958 --> 00:11:32,750
Wow. Wouldn't have expected that
from a loner like you, Uesugi.

225
00:11:32,833 --> 00:11:35,458
Well, I'm not
doing it voluntarily.

226
00:11:35,541 --> 00:11:37,791
My class is the one in charge
of the test of courage,

227
00:11:37,875 --> 00:11:39,416
and when they picked
the committee,

228
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:42,083
I was studying instead of paying
attention to the teacher,

229
00:11:42,166 --> 00:11:44,541
which meant the job
got relegated to me.

230
00:11:44,625 --> 00:11:46,458
Talk about bad luck.

231
00:11:46,541 --> 00:11:48,375
He brought it on himself.

232
00:11:49,416 --> 00:11:52,916
Oh, let them have their fun.
I'll exact my revenge soon.

233
00:11:54,083 --> 00:11:56,541
It'll be an evening
they'll never forget.

234
00:11:57,625 --> 00:11:58,750
You're committed to this.

235
00:11:58,833 --> 00:12:00,375
It wasn't very nice of them

236
00:12:00,458 --> 00:12:02,583
to make him do
all the prep work by himself.

237
00:12:02,666 --> 00:12:05,375
I'm giving Class One
a piece of my mind!

238
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:07,541
[FUTARO] Nah, don't bother.
Miku's right.

239
00:12:07,625 --> 00:12:10,250
-I did bring this upon myself.
-But still.

240
00:12:10,333 --> 00:12:12,375
[FUTARO] And besides,
it's not like I care

241
00:12:12,458 --> 00:12:13,875
about camping, anyway.

242
00:12:16,125 --> 00:12:18,125
Okay! Then let's try
to think of some things

243
00:12:18,208 --> 00:12:20,500
that'll make you
more excited about it!

244
00:12:20,583 --> 00:12:22,750
I was talking to some
other kids in my class,

245
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:24,541
and they said that
our school's camping trip has

246
00:12:24,625 --> 00:12:26,458
a special legend
to go along with it!

247
00:12:27,458 --> 00:12:29,041
On the last night,
there's always a dance

248
00:12:29,125 --> 00:12:30,083
around the campfire.

249
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:32,083
It's really fun and romantic!

250
00:12:32,166 --> 00:12:33,916
The rumors say that anybody
who's paired up

251
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,791
when the music stops
is destined to spend

252
00:12:35,875 --> 00:12:37,708
the rest of their lives
together!

253
00:12:38,791 --> 00:12:39,708
[giggles]

254
00:12:40,791 --> 00:12:42,291
[FUTARO]
That's unrealistic.

255
00:12:42,375 --> 00:12:44,333
-And stupid.
-[MIKU] Mm-hmm.

256
00:12:44,416 --> 00:12:46,166
You guys! You're such a drag!

257
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:48,458
We're talking about dancing
in the firelight

258
00:12:48,541 --> 00:12:49,958
and finding true love!

259
00:12:50,041 --> 00:12:52,416
Isn't that the least bit
exciting to you two?

260
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:55,583
-Well, time to start study--
-[ICHIKA] Yoohoo!

261
00:12:57,041 --> 00:12:58,208
[FUTARO]
Hey, you're late.

262
00:12:58,291 --> 00:13:00,041
What's the clown face for?

263
00:13:00,125 --> 00:13:01,208
[FUTARO]
Irrelevant.

264
00:13:01,291 --> 00:13:03,083
-Today's math day.
-Sorry, I can't.

265
00:13:03,166 --> 00:13:07,041
I have a shoot to go to now.
Speaking of which.

266
00:13:07,125 --> 00:13:10,166
I thought of a way to let you
know in advance next time.

267
00:13:10,250 --> 00:13:11,291
Huh?

268
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:14,541
Let's trade contact info.

269
00:13:15,666 --> 00:13:17,625
[FUTARO]
Contact info?

270
00:13:18,916 --> 00:13:20,791
I don't know
if that's necessary.

271
00:13:20,875 --> 00:13:22,833
Yeah, I think
that's a fantastic idea!

272
00:13:22,916 --> 00:13:24,333
Please, Uesugi!

273
00:13:24,416 --> 00:13:26,583
I want you to be able
to reach me anytime, too!

274
00:13:26,666 --> 00:13:28,166
Oh, but first,

275
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:30,250
there's something else
I need to take care of.

276
00:13:31,291 --> 00:13:32,625
That oughta do it.

277
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:36,375
Hmm? Yotsuba.
What are you making?

278
00:13:36,458 --> 00:13:38,333
Or should I even ask?

279
00:13:38,416 --> 00:13:40,333
[YOTSUBA]
A thousand cranes!

280
00:13:40,416 --> 00:13:42,041
They're a gift
for my friend's friend

281
00:13:42,125 --> 00:13:43,333
who's away at the hospital.

282
00:13:43,416 --> 00:13:46,166
That isn't studying!
Let me do half.

283
00:13:46,250 --> 00:13:48,166
Once we finish this,
it's straight to work!

284
00:13:48,250 --> 00:13:49,208
[YOTSUBA]
Okay.

285
00:13:49,291 --> 00:13:51,625
-[MAN] Oh, Miss Nakano.
-Huh?

286
00:13:51,708 --> 00:13:53,083
Hello, sir.

287
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:55,375
Glad I found you.

288
00:13:55,458 --> 00:13:57,458
Would you mind
putting these papers

289
00:13:57,541 --> 00:13:59,333
on everyone's desks
for me, please?

290
00:13:59,416 --> 00:14:00,708
[YOTSUBA]
Sure thing.

291
00:14:00,791 --> 00:14:02,458
[FUTARO]
Damn, how much of a pushover

292
00:14:02,541 --> 00:14:03,875
can one girl be?

293
00:14:03,958 --> 00:14:05,333
[gasps]
Wait.

294
00:14:05,416 --> 00:14:06,791
I know what she's up to!

295
00:14:06,875 --> 00:14:10,000
Is she buying time
so she doesn't have to study?

296
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:11,625
If that's her game,
then she's even more

297
00:14:11,708 --> 00:14:14,000
of a devious mastermind
than Nino!

298
00:14:14,083 --> 00:14:17,083
-'Kay, I'm off to work.
-[MIKU] Good luck.

299
00:14:17,166 --> 00:14:18,375
Yeah, break a leg, sis!

300
00:14:18,458 --> 00:14:21,041
[buzzing]

301
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:24,625
[ICHIKA] If you don't want
this photo to get around,

302
00:14:24,708 --> 00:14:27,416
then you'll have to collect
everyone's information!

303
00:14:28,833 --> 00:14:30,583
[gasps]

304
00:14:33,125 --> 00:14:34,666
[giggles]

305
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:38,416
[FUTARO] As your tutor,
I need to be more involved.

306
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:41,125
I don't know, maybe I should
get your contact info!

307
00:14:42,125 --> 00:14:43,708
[MIKU]
Sure, I can give you mine.

308
00:14:44,791 --> 00:14:47,291
Woohoo. Two down.

309
00:14:47,375 --> 00:14:49,083
I guess this means
I'll just have to try

310
00:14:49,166 --> 00:14:51,000
and get Nino's
and Itsuki's another day, then.

311
00:14:51,083 --> 00:14:53,375
[YOTSUBA] I'm pretty sure
I saw them in the cafeteria.

312
00:14:53,458 --> 00:14:55,625
-Come on, let's go!
-Hey! Don't go!

313
00:14:55,708 --> 00:14:57,000
I didn't get yours yet!

314
00:15:00,708 --> 00:15:02,916
Uh, here. I gave you mine too.

315
00:15:03,916 --> 00:15:06,250
-[MIKU] Thanks.
-[FUTARO] Yotsuba, wait up!

316
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,166
[giggles]

317
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:12,666
♪

318
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:14,083
[NINO]
Absolutely not.

319
00:15:14,166 --> 00:15:16,250
Not even
if the world was ending.

320
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,041
Yeah, I can't think
of a single reason

321
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:20,916
why we would ever want
to contact you.

322
00:15:21,958 --> 00:15:24,416
I had a feeling you would say
something rude like that.

323
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:26,333
But wait, that's not all!

324
00:15:26,416 --> 00:15:28,416
Act now and you
will receive a bonus.

325
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:31,000
Raiha's info, absolutely free!

326
00:15:31,083 --> 00:15:33,083
It's a once-in-a-lifetime offer!

327
00:15:34,125 --> 00:15:35,291
[grunts]

328
00:15:37,083 --> 00:15:39,958
[ITSUKI]
Fine, I guess I have no choice.

329
00:15:40,041 --> 00:15:42,250
I can't believe
you'd sell out your own family.

330
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:44,583
A small price to pay.

331
00:15:44,666 --> 00:15:46,666
You gonna give me yours, Nino?

332
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:48,791
[NINO]
Don't be ridiculous.

333
00:15:48,875 --> 00:15:50,791
-[FUTARO] Suit yourself.
-[NINO] Hmm?

334
00:15:52,125 --> 00:15:54,666
I guess that means
we'll have to chat without you.

335
00:15:54,750 --> 00:15:57,000
Who knows what things you're
gonna miss out on, though.

336
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:00,458
Okay. Give me something
to write it down on.

337
00:16:00,541 --> 00:16:01,833
[FUTARO chuckles]

338
00:16:03,166 --> 00:16:04,125
Here you go.

339
00:16:05,541 --> 00:16:06,833
Good job, Uesugi.

340
00:16:06,916 --> 00:16:08,291
Now you've got everyone's.

341
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:10,833
You wanna check your math there?

342
00:16:10,916 --> 00:16:11,958
Huh?

343
00:16:12,041 --> 00:16:15,375
Ichika. Miku.
Itsuki. Nino.

344
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:20,166
Yotsuba! That's me! Bingo!

345
00:16:20,250 --> 00:16:22,208
[FUTARO]
Her stupidity scares me.

346
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:26,083
Here, go ahead
and take mine too, then.

347
00:16:27,166 --> 00:16:28,625
[buzzing]

348
00:16:28,708 --> 00:16:29,875
[FUTARO]
Somebody's calling you.

349
00:16:29,958 --> 00:16:31,000
Huh?

350
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:35,875
The basketball club captain?
What does she want?

351
00:16:35,958 --> 00:16:37,000
I thought you were done.

352
00:16:37,083 --> 00:16:38,666
Uh...

353
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:40,250
Um, almost.

354
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:42,750
I had one tiny thing left
to do for them, that's all.

355
00:16:42,833 --> 00:16:44,875
Oh, gosh, would you look
at the time!

356
00:16:44,958 --> 00:16:46,958
Sorry, Uesugi,
but I gotta go now!

357
00:16:48,208 --> 00:16:50,625
[FUTARO] Again, that girl is
a terrible liar.

358
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:53,208
[FUTARO grunts]

359
00:16:53,291 --> 00:16:54,541
Hey!

360
00:16:55,875 --> 00:16:57,916
I wrote my info down for you.

361
00:17:01,791 --> 00:17:03,458
Hey there, everybody,
how's it going?

362
00:17:03,541 --> 00:17:06,208
Hi, Nakano. Thanks for helping
us out the other day.

363
00:17:06,291 --> 00:17:07,458
Don't mention it.

364
00:17:08,666 --> 00:17:10,000
[FUTARO]
I knew it.

365
00:17:10,083 --> 00:17:12,375
She must have had
some important business here

366
00:17:12,458 --> 00:17:13,750
to tell such an obvious lie.

367
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:15,458
[GIRL]
Anyway, I wanted to ask,

368
00:17:15,541 --> 00:17:17,750
have you given any thought
to joining the club for real?

369
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:19,250
[gasps]

370
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:22,250
I have. Thank you so much
for inviting me.

371
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:24,750
[FUTARO]
So that's what this is about!

372
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:27,250
Turns out Yotsuba
really was trying to find a way

373
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:29,000
to weasel out
of our study sessions!

374
00:17:29,083 --> 00:17:31,750
That's great news! So, uh...

375
00:17:31,833 --> 00:17:33,041
[YOTSUBA]
Well...

376
00:17:34,875 --> 00:17:36,250
I'm sorry, but...

377
00:17:41,250 --> 00:17:42,791
I'm gonna have to say no.

378
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:48,375
I know you and the rest
of the team really need my help

379
00:17:48,458 --> 00:17:50,416
and I'm letting all of you down,

380
00:17:50,500 --> 00:17:53,291
but I have something important
in the afternoons now.

381
00:17:53,375 --> 00:17:55,791
[ALL gasp]

382
00:17:55,875 --> 00:17:57,666
Um, but if you want,

383
00:17:57,750 --> 00:18:00,291
I could still fill in
whenever you have a game.

384
00:18:00,375 --> 00:18:03,791
Well, that's that.
I can't force you to join us.

385
00:18:03,875 --> 00:18:06,125
Although I think
it's a huge waste of talent

386
00:18:06,208 --> 00:18:07,250
not to have you.

387
00:18:08,833 --> 00:18:10,958
I don't have any talent at all,

388
00:18:11,041 --> 00:18:13,333
but there's somebody
who pushes me anyway.

389
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:15,875
♪

390
00:18:19,291 --> 00:18:20,375
[YOTSUBA sighs]

391
00:18:22,375 --> 00:18:23,333
Huh!

392
00:18:24,458 --> 00:18:28,125
Oh. Hey, Uesugi.
What brings you here?

393
00:18:28,208 --> 00:18:29,833
I was on my way to the library.

394
00:18:30,958 --> 00:18:32,333
Okay, but this club wing's

395
00:18:32,416 --> 00:18:34,375
in the totally opposite
direction of the library.

396
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:37,333
That's kinda weird.

397
00:18:37,416 --> 00:18:40,375
Are you done
with what you came here for?

398
00:18:40,458 --> 00:18:43,208
I'm gonna keep working you hard,
so be ready.

399
00:18:44,791 --> 00:18:45,791
Right!

400
00:18:48,791 --> 00:18:50,166
I can handle it!

401
00:18:52,583 --> 00:18:54,291
[FUTARO]
Thank you, Raiha.

402
00:18:54,375 --> 00:18:55,750
[RAIHA]
No prob!

403
00:18:55,833 --> 00:18:57,291
Oh, I forgot.

404
00:18:58,458 --> 00:19:01,083
I should probably message
the quints and let them know

405
00:19:01,166 --> 00:19:03,500
about the weekend session
I'm planning for them.

406
00:19:03,583 --> 00:19:06,166
Wait. Just four?

407
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:09,250
[gasps]
My student handbook!

408
00:19:11,916 --> 00:19:14,000
Did I never get it back
from her?

409
00:19:16,291 --> 00:19:20,208
♪

410
00:19:20,291 --> 00:19:21,791
[snoring softly]

411
00:19:21,875 --> 00:19:23,750
[footsteps approaching]

412
00:19:23,833 --> 00:19:26,083
♪

413
00:19:31,166 --> 00:19:33,791
Give me
my student handbook, now.

414
00:19:33,875 --> 00:19:36,291
♪

415
00:19:36,375 --> 00:19:38,750
[NINO]
Get out!

416
00:19:40,125 --> 00:19:42,958
♪

417
00:19:43,041 --> 00:19:44,625
You're unbelievable.

418
00:19:44,708 --> 00:19:46,083
What kind of creep barges

419
00:19:46,166 --> 00:19:48,000
into a young lady's bedroom
without permission?

420
00:19:48,083 --> 00:19:49,666
Well, I gave him permission.

421
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:51,541
Yeah, and what gives you
the right to do that?

422
00:19:51,625 --> 00:19:53,833
Listen, I apologize.

423
00:19:53,916 --> 00:19:56,541
I only did it because I need
my student handbook back

424
00:19:56,625 --> 00:19:58,125
as soon as possible.

425
00:19:58,208 --> 00:20:00,083
You're not usually so meek.

426
00:20:00,166 --> 00:20:02,625
You must be hiding something
important in this thing.

427
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:06,083
[FUTARO]
If she sees that old photo,

428
00:20:06,166 --> 00:20:08,583
there's no telling
what she'll do to me.

429
00:20:08,666 --> 00:20:11,125
Good morning, Futaro.

430
00:20:11,208 --> 00:20:12,500
Oh, and Nino.

431
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,458
You wanted this, right?

432
00:20:15,541 --> 00:20:16,958
You sure you can do it?

433
00:20:17,041 --> 00:20:19,500
What? I told you
of course I can!

434
00:20:19,583 --> 00:20:20,750
I'm not a baby.

435
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,458
[scoffs]

436
00:20:30,541 --> 00:20:31,625
Wha...

437
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:35,000
[NINO] Any other time,
I'd rather drop dead

438
00:20:35,083 --> 00:20:37,041
than let you into my room.

439
00:20:37,125 --> 00:20:40,541
Fine, I'll leave,
as soon as I get my handbook.

440
00:20:43,666 --> 00:20:45,125
Here's the deal.

441
00:20:45,208 --> 00:20:47,000
I'll give it back to you
if you pierce my ears for me.

442
00:20:47,083 --> 00:20:49,000
Wha...

443
00:20:49,083 --> 00:20:51,291
Do you want
your stupid book or not?

444
00:20:51,375 --> 00:20:52,708
Let's get it over with.

445
00:20:52,791 --> 00:20:54,750
Uh. Just do it yourself.

446
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:57,291
Yeah, no thanks!
Too scary.

447
00:20:57,375 --> 00:20:59,208
Then why do you want it
done at all?

448
00:20:59,291 --> 00:21:02,291
Look, it'll hurt for a while,
are you prepared for that?

449
00:21:02,375 --> 00:21:03,583
Oh, what do you know?

450
00:21:03,666 --> 00:21:06,000
It's not like
you've had it done before.

451
00:21:06,083 --> 00:21:08,041
[FUTARO]
Uh, that's true.

452
00:21:08,125 --> 00:21:09,583
[NINO]
I just want it, okay.

453
00:21:10,583 --> 00:21:13,500
I guess it's because
everyone else I know has it.

454
00:21:13,583 --> 00:21:14,791
[FUTARO]
Okay.

455
00:21:15,833 --> 00:21:16,958
Fine then.

456
00:21:17,041 --> 00:21:20,250
♪

457
00:21:20,333 --> 00:21:22,458
I can't think of
a better opportunity

458
00:21:22,541 --> 00:21:25,375
to get back at you
for the grief you've caused.

459
00:21:25,458 --> 00:21:26,583
Here goes.

460
00:21:28,125 --> 00:21:29,625
I need that book.

461
00:21:30,625 --> 00:21:34,041
♪

462
00:21:34,125 --> 00:21:39,791
[FUTARO] Five. Four.
Three. Two.

463
00:21:39,875 --> 00:21:43,416
One. Zero!

464
00:21:43,500 --> 00:21:45,291
Is what I'll say, okay?

465
00:21:45,375 --> 00:21:47,041
[NINO]
Quit messing with me!

466
00:21:47,125 --> 00:21:51,833
[screaming in pain]

467
00:21:52,958 --> 00:21:54,708
-[FUTARO] Oh, crap!
-Huh?

468
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,541
Whoa, he looks like a bad boy.

469
00:22:06,125 --> 00:22:09,166
He's exactly my type!
Who is this?

470
00:22:09,250 --> 00:22:10,458
[FUTARO]
That'd be me!

471
00:22:10,541 --> 00:22:13,000
Um, he's one of my relatives.

472
00:22:13,083 --> 00:22:15,541
But that picture
was taken a while ago, so...

473
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:17,375
Wow.

474
00:22:17,458 --> 00:22:20,083
Well, I can tell who got all
the good looks in your family!

475
00:22:20,166 --> 00:22:21,666
Think you could
set me up with him?

476
00:22:23,541 --> 00:22:25,916
Maybe. Eventually.

477
00:22:27,250 --> 00:22:28,666
[NINO]
Oh, yeah!

478
00:22:28,750 --> 00:22:30,583
My sisters and I used to be
adorable little angels

479
00:22:30,666 --> 00:22:32,208
back in the day, too.

480
00:22:34,083 --> 00:22:36,125
See? Hey, look at it.

481
00:22:37,833 --> 00:22:39,750
Not interested, huh?

482
00:22:39,833 --> 00:22:42,375
I think I'll go show it to
the girls for old times' sake.

483
00:22:44,791 --> 00:22:46,666
That was close.

484
00:22:49,708 --> 00:22:51,916
Oh. Done already?

485
00:22:53,083 --> 00:22:54,791
Well, I gave it
some more thought,

486
00:22:54,875 --> 00:22:56,791
and I decided
I shouldn't rush it.

487
00:22:56,875 --> 00:22:58,500
As long as I have pierced ears

488
00:22:58,583 --> 00:23:01,083
by the time I'm wearing
my wedding dress, I'll be happy.

489
00:23:02,958 --> 00:23:05,375
Anyway, check out
this blast from the past!

490
00:23:05,458 --> 00:23:08,041
[YOTSUBA] Oh, wow,
we look so young there!

491
00:23:08,125 --> 00:23:10,416
[FUTARO] Well, she ended up
seeing my photo.

492
00:23:11,833 --> 00:23:14,000
Good thing it was only half.

493
00:23:14,083 --> 00:23:16,083
[YOTSUBA]
Aw, we were so adorable!

494
00:23:16,166 --> 00:23:17,750
[ICHIKA]
When was this taken?

495
00:23:17,833 --> 00:23:19,416
[MIKU]
In sixth grade.

496
00:23:21,958 --> 00:23:23,625
[ICHIKA]
This was Kyoto,

497
00:23:23,708 --> 00:23:25,458
so it must have been
from our school trip.

498
00:23:26,958 --> 00:23:28,875
[FUTARO]
Five years, huh?

499
00:23:28,958 --> 00:23:30,416
The color's fading a little.

500
00:23:35,083 --> 00:23:37,041
[YOTSUBA]
This takes me back!

501
00:23:37,125 --> 00:23:38,250
[ITSUKI]
We've really changed a lot

502
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:39,916
since those days, haven't we?

503
00:23:51,041 --> 00:23:52,500
[FUTARO]
I hope we meet again.

504
00:24:00,333 --> 00:24:01,875
[QUINTUPLETS]
Quintuplet Trivia!

505
00:24:01,958 --> 00:24:03,291
[MIKU]
Yotsuba's the sporty one.

506
00:24:03,375 --> 00:24:04,625
[NINO]
But does she know all the rules?

507
00:24:04,708 --> 00:24:05,958
[YOTSUBA]
Huh? Sure I do!

508
00:24:06,041 --> 00:24:07,500
[ICHIKA] What are the rules
for basketball?

509
00:24:07,583 --> 00:24:08,750
[YOTSUBA]
Put the ball in the basket,

510
00:24:08,833 --> 00:24:09,708
and you get two or three points!

511
00:24:09,791 --> 00:24:11,083
[MIKU]
That's it?

512
00:24:11,166 --> 00:24:12,750
Oh, and after practice,
you always eat a snack!

513
00:24:12,833 --> 00:24:14,583
[NINO] I don't think
that's a requirement!

